						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing in ‘Paḍumala-gadde’ at Nayilāḍi.</p>						

						<p>Virūpāksha, 1472 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly dameged record gives the date and refers to <hi rend="bold">Viṭharasa-oḍeya</hi> who is said to have been governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru.</hi> It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1395 (current), Nandana, Māgaśira ba. 1(1)</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1472 A.D., November 16.</hi> The details are, however, not verifiable.</p>						

						</summary>
